title: Trump calls on Fed to turn U.S. economy into 'rocket ship' - POLITICO
content: Trump here is showing his economic ignorance in telling the Fed to lower interest rates because of strong employment number this quarter. The country is at near manufacturing capacity and lowering rates will put pressure on prices. Once inflation gets started you can't turn it off quickly, it spreads through the economy and takes many months to tamp down, if then. We now have low inflation and when that ends, we likely will return to more normal rates in the 4% range. This is what Trump is risking as workers wages don't keep up with rising prices. The collateral problem is the national debt that is ballooned under Trump. Its creating instability in the economy and is the source of much of this 'forced' employment and good economic news. The bubble can burst with the next crises and put us into a downturn. With low interest rates now and even lower one's as Trump is demanding, the Fed has no brakes left to throw to stem it and is in new territory with still a large balance sheet of debt it put on in the last recovery. The Fed is being boxed in and Trump is ignoring it all as he is pushing us up to and over the cliff.
